 0961: # w = window size; two items appear within +/- w steps of each other (where w=1 means adjacent items)
 0962: # f = filter frequency; if two items don't fall within the same window more than f times, then no edge is inferred
 0963: # c = confidence interval; retain the edge if there is a <= c probability that two items occur within the same window n times by chance alone
 0964: # valid=(0,1); ensures that graph can produce data using censored RW.
 0965: #              potentially a lot more computationally intensive, but could produce better fit
